#
#   IPW-3 Cut/Slice DATA SUBMITTAL FORM for Test Case ###, May 4th 2026
#
#  
#
#
#       NOMENCLATURE:
#                  X [m]:  X-coordinate of the surface (clean for reference)
#                  Y [m]:  Y-coordinate of the surface (clean for reference)
#                  Z [m]:  Z-coordinate of the surface (clean for reference)
#             X_ICED [m]:  X-coordinate of the ice surface (1/1 layer only)
#             Y_ICED [m]:  Y-coordinate of the ice surface (1/1 layer only)
#             Z_ICED [m]:  Z-coordinate of the ice surface (1/1 layer only)
#                  s [m]:  Wrap distance from high-light on surface (X, Y, Z)
#                 Cp [-]:  Pressure coefficient
#            HTC [W/m2K]:  Convective Heat Transfer Coefficient
#               Beta [-]:  Collection efficiency
#                 Ts [K]:  Surface temperature
#                 FF [-]:  Freezing fraction
#                  k [m]:  Surface roughness height (OPTIONAL)
#         RhoIce [kg/m3]:  Ice density (OPTIONAL)
#      HTC_CLEAN [W/m2K]:  Convective Heat Transfer Coefficient on the surface without roughness (OPTIONAL)
#
#                XXX:   Participant ID (assigned by IPW committee); e.g., 001, 020, 147
#                ###:   Test case name (NACA0012_AE3932, NACA0012_3933, ONERAM6)
#            DATASET:   Sequential number, should start at 01 for each participant 
#
#    E.g. TITLE field could be: 001_NACA0012_AE3932_03 for the third submission by participant 1 for the case NACA0012_AE3932
#
#
#    FLOW CONDITIONS:
#                        AOA : 4.0 deg
#                 Mach Number: 0.3114 [-]
#                         MAC: 0.5334 [m]
#             Reynolds Number: 3.8441 million (based on MAC)
#             Freestream Temp: XXX [K]
#              Reference area: 0.97548 [m2]
#     Moment Reference Center: 0.13335, 0, 0 [m] (X, Y, Z)
#
#              NOTES: 1. Please use at least 5 decimal places in the numerical values
#                     2. If data are NOT provided, please fill data fields with a numerical value of "-999" 
#
#+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

